Package UserCode.pets

Interface Summary
IBehaviour IBehaviour: the interface for any behaviour.
IBehaviourMgr IBehaviourMgr: A manager of a set of IBehaviours
IFoodMgr IFoodMgr: a thing that takes care of creating food tokens and their behaviours.
IRenderable IRenderable defines the interface for all renderable items within a JFF simulation.
IRenderableFactory IRenderableFactory: specifically to create Tokens.
 

Class Summary
Behaviour Abstract class Behaviour - all common code required for implementing behaviours.
BehaviourMgr BehaviourMgr: implementation of IBehaviour - a manager of a set of IBehaviours.
FoodBehaviour FoodBehaviour - implements movement behaviour for fish food.
FoodMgr FoodMgr: a thing that takes care of foods and their behaviours.
Renderable The Renderable class provides all properties/behaviour to display a renderable in an Env3D simulation.
RenderableFactory RenderableFactory: a helper class to create displayable renderable.
RenderableTest The test class RenderableTest, for testing Renderable.
 

Exception Summary
ArgumentOutOfBoundsException The ArgumentOutOfBoundsException class: used to flag when a parameter is outside the defined range of values.
